      <abstract> Reverend Eddie K. Edwards was a Christian preacher in Detroit, Mich. With his wife Minister Mary Edwards, in 1976 he founded the Joy of Jesus faith-based nonprofit organization in Detroit. The ministry sought to help urban youth through a summer camp and other activities. The collection includes ten recordings of interviews and television programs featuring Rev. Eddie K. Edwards, Joy of Jesus publications, biographical information about Rev. Edwards, as well as papers related to the ministry of Minister Mary D. Edwards. </abstract>
